Title: Associate Degree of Education
Description: Learn more about how our Associate Degree of Education introduces you to university study and prepares you for guaranteed entry into our Bachelor of Education (Primary) degree, with credit.
Location: Bldg A, Room A3.45, Flexible Learning Centre

Title: Primary teaching
Description: Discover the rewards of studying a primary teaching degree. Hear our friendly staff discuss selection, course information and career options.
Location: Bldg A, Room A3.45, Flexible Learning Centre

Location: Bldg A, Room A3.45, Flexible Learning Centre

Title: Primary teaching

Location: Bldg A, Room A3.45, Flexible Learning Centre

Title: Visit the library
Description: Explore our library by taking a look around, or join a casual tour upon request. Discover what makes our students love the library and learn about the spaces, facilities and services available.

Title: Discover Deakin
Description: Find out all about the study options, exciting opportunities and experiences awaiting you at Deakin. Learn how our students are prepared for future career opportunities, and get tips on how to make the most of your Open Day visit.

Title: Commerce
Description: Discover what it's like to study our internationally recognised and EPAS accredited commerce degree. Combine a solid foundation in business with your choice of professional majors including marketing, HR management, economics, financial planning and accounting.

Title: Pathways to Deakin
Description: The traditional path from Year 12 to university isn't the only way to Deakin. Learn more about our alternate pathways to starting your dream degree at Deakin, either through courses at Deakin, with our partner Deakin College or our TAFE partners across Victoria.

Title: Life at Deakin
Description: Thinking about studying at Deakin but not sure what to expect? Take a walk through our student experience from your offer to your first exam and find out what a typical day might look like for you.

Title: Returning to study as mature-age and non-Year 12 students
Description: Looking to return to study? This session provides a guide on choosing the right course for you and tips on how to navigate the application process. Learn how study can suit your lifestyle, with flexible delivery options to help juggle work and your life commitments.

Title: Money matters
Description: Learn everything you need to know about tuition fees, invoicing and HECS-HELP. Discover if you are eligible for a scholarship and how to apply.

Title: Understanding VTAC's SEAS
Description: Find out all you need to know about VTAC's Special Entry and Access Scheme (SEAS) from our specialists, including the application process, different SEAS categories and how SEAS impacts university selection.

Title: Nursing and midwifery clinical simulation centre
Description: Visit our purpose-built learning spaces and simulated clinical spaces, which closely replicate hospital and community environments. Drop in any time to observe our state-of-the-art 3G SimMan patient manikin programmed to simulate a variety of patient scenarios, and chat with academic staff and students to learn more about our courses and equipment.

Title: Campus tours
Description: Join one of our tours to discover more of the Warrnambool campus. Led by our Student Ambassadors who know all the ins and outs of Deakin, you'll get a feel for campus life while learning more about our study areas, state-of-the-art facilities, and how to make the best transition into university.

Title: Yolla, our marine research vessel
Description: Explore our research vessel, Yolla, and gain an insight into our unique marine habitats.

Title: Win with Deakin
Description: Enter your details to receive updates on exciting Deakin news, events and courses. Just for registering, you can spin to win instant prizes, including Deakin hoodies, beanies, bags and lollies. Find us on campus for your opportunity to walk away a winner!

Title: Marine biology
Description: Our marine courses at Warrnambool and Geelong offer students access to a classroom without walls, with a wide range of aquatic environments and diverse marine life right on the campus doorstep at Warrnambool, and at the Queenscliff Marine Research Center at Geelong. Learn how fieldwork and industry placements will prepare you for a rewarding career.
Location: Bldg J, Room J2.01, Alfred Deakin Lecture Theatre

Interest_area: Health sciences and allied health; Psychology
Title: Psychology and health sciences
Description: Interested in studying psychology or health sciences? Join us to learn how our psychology courses expose you to the biological, developmental, social and cognitive factors that affect how humans think, feel and behave, and the countless career pathways available. You'll also discover how our Bachelor of Health Sciences focuses on getting you ready to tackle the biggest issues in health - and prepares you for career opportunities which will allow you to make a difference in the largest growing employment industry in Australia.
Location: Bldg J, Room J2.01, Alfred Deakin Lecture Theatre

Title: Nursing and midwifery
Description: Our nursing and midwifery courses are delivered by a school ranked in the top 1% in the world. Students graduate in demand, with the knowledge, skills and professionalism to work as a registered nurse and/or midwife. Our courses will prepare you to provide high-quality, patient-centred care in a range of areas including acute/sub-acute care, medical and surgical care, maternity care, aged care, rehabilitation, paediatrics, community nursing, and mental health nursing (QS World University Rankings by Subject 2018).
Location: Bldg J, Room J2.01, Alfred Deakin Lecture Theatre

Title: Marine biology, fisheries and aquaculture display
Description: Explore our environmental science display and learn about our marine biology course and potential graduate employment opportunities. Academic staff and researchers in marine biology will demonstrate our exciting new research equipment and be on hand to answer any questions.
Location: Bldg J, Room J2.27 and Bldg E

Title: Drone obstacle course
Description: Come and test your flying skills in our mini-drone obstacle course for your chance to win some great prizes. You will also learn about the new unit we offer at Warrnambool, landscape drones, where we teach students to use drones for real-world industry purposes.

Title: Test your robotics skills
Description: Come and experience first-hand what it is like to attend a Deakin Warrnambool STEM Camp. Test your 21st century skills by exploring digital technologies with some hands-on robotics using our Sphero robots.

Title: Aquatic research facility tour
Description: Visit our recently refurbished aquatic research facility and observe various species of fish in the hatchery, salt water and fresh water areas.
Location: Departing from the Environment booth, Career and Course Information Centre

Title: Deakin residences tours
Description: Join in on one of our residence tours and discover the different types of accommodation available at our Warrnambool Campus. Learn from the experts just what it's like to live near campus and how you can become part of our close-knit resident community.
Location: Departing from the Accommodation booth, Career and Course Information Centre

Title: Football round robin
Description: Watch brilliance in the making as the rising stars of the Deakin University Female Football League show off their skills in an exhibition round robin. Teams from around the region will battle it out for the Deakin Warrnambool Open Day Pennant Flag.
